  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIAS Sexual and Gender Based Violence Prevention and Response Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective #1: To sustain a robust advocacy and community-based referral network that identifies, responds to and prevents sexual and gender-based violence (SGBV).  
Objective #2: To respond to SGBV through protection and psychosocial support that alleviates the related effects of trauma and violence suffered by refugees (men and women) in their quest for durable solutions, as well as to create prevention mechanisms by promoting dignified livelihoods for persons with specific needs and victims of SGBV. 100% of reporting rape survivors referred to medical partners with the provision to give post-exposure prophylaxis (PEP) with 72 hours.   
*Persons with specific needs (PSN) include: widows with children, teenage mothers, persons with disabilities, older and homebound individuals, and youth at risk.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees, vulnerable victims of torture/sexual and gender based violence</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support refugees in eastern Chad by  providing (1) a sustainable advocacy and community-based referral system that identifies and prevents Sexual Gender Based Violence (SGBV) (2)  psychosocial support to male and female survivors, and (3) empowerment for women and girl towards increased self-reliance, leadership and decision making abilities</narrative>
  </description>
